  "detailed_description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Watermelon (with a broken head) Game is a thrilling and exhilarating physics-based puzzle game inspired by polyomino puzzles and the Suika Game.</strong></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/9ef20ff379f0b92e1217f5ec97070e6c.poster.avif?t=1768978976\" width=584 height=328 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/9ef20ff379f0b92e1217f5ec97070e6c.webm?t=1768978976\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/9ef20ff379f0b92e1217f5ec97070e6c.mp4?t=1768978976\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >This game follows the journey of a head-injured watermelon as it seeks to recover its lost emotions. Each block represents an emotion, and merging identical blocks evolves them into the next stage of emotion.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" ><strong>Strategically Drop Blocks!</strong></h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/b0e3de2370b877dcc8ac163f7ef929fe.poster.avif?t=1768978976\" width=584 height=328 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/b0e3de2370b877dcc8ac163f7ef929fe.webm?t=1768978976\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/b0e3de2370b877dcc8ac163f7ef929fe.mp4?t=1768978976\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >You can rotate and flip blocks to strategically drop them into the desired position.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/5068fa03a3bbdc46df1fdb2cfe256f4b.poster.avif?t=1768978976\" width=584 height=328 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/5068fa03a3bbdc46df1fdb2cfe256f4b.webm?t=1768978976\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/5068fa03a3bbdc46df1fdb2cfe256f4b.mp4?t=1768978976\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Although the space is limited, the blocks are made up of straight lines and right angles, allowing you to interlock them, balance, and stack them as you play.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" ><strong>Rotate the Watermelon!</strong></h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/feb6409974b05fec3960edbbbdfbe394.poster.avif?t=1768978976\" width=584 height=328 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/feb6409974b05fec3960edbbbdfbe394.webm?t=1768978976\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/feb6409974b05fec3960edbbbdfbe394.mp4?t=1768978976\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >You can rotate the watermelon to move the blocks.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/775e5e1987b681ebe301f28538605e9b.poster.avif?t=1768978976\" width=584 height=328 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/775e5e1987b681ebe301f28538605e9b.webm?t=1768978976\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/775e5e1987b681ebe301f28538605e9b.mp4?t=1768978976\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Use this to create gaps between blocks.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/c7d01b9865618c5786d76b15e108953f.poster.avif?t=1768978976\" width=584 height=328 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/c7d01b9865618c5786d76b15e108953f.webm?t=1768978976\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/c7d01b9865618c5786d76b15e108953f.mp4?t=1768978976\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >You can also merge the blocks inside the watermelon (though it's not easy!).</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/2372b58e7c217388cffa817329f934b2.poster.avif?t=1768978976\" width=584 height=328 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/2372b58e7c217388cffa817329f934b2.webm?t=1768978976\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/2372b58e7c217388cffa817329f934b2.mp4?t=1768978976\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Be careful, as you might accidentally drop more blocks out of the container if you're not careful!</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >bgm: spring day by syncopika, CC-BY 3.0, from </p>",
  "about_the_game": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Watermelon (with a broken head) Game is a thrilling and exhilarating physics-based puzzle game inspired by polyomino puzzles and the Suika Game.</strong></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/9ef20ff379f0b92e1217f5ec97070e6c.poster.avif?t=1768978976\" width=584 height=328 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/9ef20ff379f0b92e1217f5ec97070e6c.webm?t=1768978976\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/9ef20ff379f0b92e1217f5ec97070e6c.mp4?t=1768978976\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >This game follows the journey of a head-injured watermelon as it seeks to recover its lost emotions. Each block represents an emotion, and merging identical blocks evolves them into the next stage of emotion.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" ><strong>Strategically Drop Blocks!</strong></h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/b0e3de2370b877dcc8ac163f7ef929fe.poster.avif?t=1768978976\" width=584 height=328 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/b0e3de2370b877dcc8ac163f7ef929fe.webm?t=1768978976\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/b0e3de2370b877dcc8ac163f7ef929fe.mp4?t=1768978976\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >You can rotate and flip blocks to strategically drop them into the desired position.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/5068fa03a3bbdc46df1fdb2cfe256f4b.poster.avif?t=1768978976\" width=584 height=328 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/5068fa03a3bbdc46df1fdb2cfe256f4b.webm?t=1768978976\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/5068fa03a3bbdc46df1fdb2cfe256f4b.mp4?t=1768978976\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Although the space is limited, the blocks are made up of straight lines and right angles, allowing you to interlock them, balance, and stack them as you play.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" ><strong>Rotate the Watermelon!</strong></h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/feb6409974b05fec3960edbbbdfbe394.poster.avif?t=1768978976\" width=584 height=328 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/feb6409974b05fec3960edbbbdfbe394.webm?t=1768978976\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/feb6409974b05fec3960edbbbdfbe394.mp4?t=1768978976\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >You can rotate the watermelon to move the blocks.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/775e5e1987b681ebe301f28538605e9b.poster.avif?t=1768978976\" width=584 height=328 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/775e5e1987b681ebe301f28538605e9b.webm?t=1768978976\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/775e5e1987b681ebe301f28538605e9b.mp4?t=1768978976\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Use this to create gaps between blocks.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/c7d01b9865618c5786d76b15e108953f.poster.avif?t=1768978976\" width=584 height=328 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/c7d01b9865618c5786d76b15e108953f.webm?t=1768978976\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/c7d01b9865618c5786d76b15e108953f.mp4?t=1768978976\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >You can also merge the blocks inside the watermelon (though it's not easy!).</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/2372b58e7c217388cffa817329f934b2.poster.avif?t=1768978976\" width=584 height=328 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/2372b58e7c217388cffa817329f934b2.webm?t=1768978976\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3540460/extras/2372b58e7c217388cffa817329f934b2.mp4?t=1768978976\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Be careful, as you might accidentally drop more blocks out of the container if you're not careful!</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >bgm: spring day by syncopika, CC-BY 3.0, from </p>",
